All AF2 from MQTT to InfluxDB (7) (2) (2)
Asset Manager Integrator
info:
# Automatic deploy a device to the Asset Manager Dashboard 


This Node can be used before an InfluxDB (1.8) Node that uses an array with Field Keys and Tag Keys as payload. [{Field Keys},{Tag Keys}] 

## Integration to InfluxDB

This Node will automatically check the available assets and deploy any new asset within the measurement "AssetManager" on the database "data".

## Required Inputs


### DeviceName


The Tag Key "DeviceName" is required in msg.payload[1] (e.g. payload: [{},{DeviceName: XXX}])

If msg.measurement is defined it will be added as additional "tag". If not it will be "undefined"


## Usage


### Picture


By inserting a string with a standard Bas64 encoded Image in the "data:image/" format to the picture input it will be uploaded for any new Device automatically. Use small pictures < 1MB or make a small screenshot. To encode go to [Convert to Base 64](https://base64.guru/converter/encode/image) upload a file and choose the output format "Data URI".

Picture string will be checked. Node status in red will indicate wrong Picture string after any inject.


### Description


Enter any basic string for the Description.


### Geohash


Enter a 9 Digit Value for a basic Geohash. Default is "100000000"

Retrieve a Geo location from Google maps by right clicking on any stop and selecting the LNG, LAT value. [Convert it to Geohash](http://geohash.co/) with precision 9.

Geohash length will be checked. Node status in red will indicate wrong Picture string after any inject.
outputLabels: Asset Data that was send to Database

name: AF2 Simulation (2)
info:
# Aventics AF2 Flow Sensor MQTT DEMO

### Input
This node needs as Input an inject node with a timestamp in msg.payload. To really simulate an AF2 a repeat interval should be chosen. The traffic and resource demand can be limited by choosing a 0.5 to 1s interval for the injection. Disable the inject node when the Demo is not needed anymore to reduce traffic and the need for resources.

By injection of an msg.topic including "RESET_SENSOR" as a string it will reset the sensor and all values to 0.

### Input Properties

**Sensor name**
You can choose a sensor name to identify the AF2 Sensor within Node Red. It will be send as Topic in the output msg.topic.

**Flow Rate**
Enter the Range in which the Flow should outputted. Input Format is l/min. It will be outputted in m³/h.

**Temperature**
Enter the Range in which the Temperature should be outputted. Input/output format is °C.

**Pressure**
Enter the Range in which the Pressure should be outputted. Input/output format is bar.

**Connection**
Chose the Connection of your AF2 Flow Sensor. It will impact the output of the flow velocity due to different Diameters of the internal piping.

**Weekend**
If selected it will reduce the Volumetic Flow rate to 0 and the pressure to a steady value in the middle of min and max on Saturdays and Sundays.

### Output Format

As the original AF2 Flow Sensor this Demo Delivers the following consistent output Format. All formatting to other units must be done in the Visualization afterwards.

 - MassFlowRate        : kg/h
 - FlowVelocity        : m/s
 - Volume              : m³
 - VolumetricFlowRate  : m³/h
 - Mass                : kg
 - Energy              : kWh
 - Temperature         : °C
 - Pressure            : bar

### Outputs

**Output 1:** Delivers the FULL AF2 Data with statistics like min, max and mean and the corresponding units.
An additional function node is needed to prepare the data as Input to a Database.

**Output 2:** Delivers only the values of the measurements and can be directly inputted to most database nodes in node red.

func:
let owner = msg.owner 

let device = msg.device

let type = msg.type

let version = msg.version
let sensorName = msg.sensorName
let group = msg.group
let deviceNumber = parseInt(device.substr(2, 8))
let measurement = "AF" //For all Airflow Sensors

//Initialising the Asset with no Output
let asset = []
let digitalLabel = []

// General AF2 Informations

let general = [
    {
    Certificates: "CE declaration of conformity, RoHS",
    MeasurePricipalFlow: "Calorimetric",
    MeasurePricipalTemperature: "PT1200",
    MeasurePricipalPressure: "Piezoresistive",
    PressureMin: "0bar, 0psi",
    PressureMax : "16bar, 232psi",
    AmbientTemperatureMin : "-20°C, -4°F",
    AmbientTemperatureMax: "60°C, 140°F",
    ConnectionElectrical: "M12x1,8-pin,X-coded",
    MediumTemperatureMin : "-20°C, -4°F",
    MediumTemperatureMax : "60°C, 140°F",
    MaxRelHumidity: "<= 90% RF, non condensing",
    MediaSupported: "Compressed air, Argon, Nitrogen, Helium, Carbon Dioxide",
    FilterPorosity: " 5µm",
    DCVoltageMin: "36VDC",
    DCVoltageMax: "57VDC",
    PowerConsumptionMax: "<12W @ 24VDC",
    ResponseTime: "<10ms",
    ProtectionClass: "IP65, IP67 according to IEC 60529",
    ShortCircuitResistance: "Short circuit resistance",
    ShockResistanceMax: "30 g, 11 ms",
    VibrationResistance: "1 g (10 - 2000 Hz) IEC 60068 - 2-6",
    Reproducibility: "+ - 1.5% of the measured value",
    MTTF: ">50 Years",
    ProductText: "FlowMeter",
    },
    {
    VendorName: "AVENTICS",
    VendorText: "Emerson Automation Solutions",
    ProductName: "AF2",
    }
]

let AS2 = [
    {
    FlowRangeMin: "5l/min, 0.3m^3/h",
    FlowRangeMax: "1060l/min, 63.6m^3/h",
    FlowRangeExtended: "1590l/min, 95,4m^3/h",
    FlowRangeViewMax: "3180l/min, 190.8m^3/h",
    Weight: "1.23kg"
    },
    {
    ProductID: "R412026837",
    ConnectionMedium : "G3/8"
    }
    ]

let AS3 = [
    {
    FlowRangeMin: "8l/min, 0.48m^3/h",
    FlowRangeMax: "1630l/min, 97.8m^3/h",
    FlowRangeExtended: "2445l/min, 146.7m^3/h",
    FlowRangeViewMax: "4890l/min, 293.4m^3/h",
    Weight: "2.05kg",
    },
    {
    ProductID: "R412026838",
    ConnectionMedium: "G1/2"
    }
]

let AS5 = [
    {
    FlowRangeMin: "22l/min, 1.32m^3/h",
    FlowRangeMax: "4326l/min, 259.56m^3/h",
    FlowRangeExtended: "6590l/min, 395.4m^3/h",
    FlowRangeViewMax: "12980l/min, 778.8m^3/h",
    Weight: "2.97kg",
    },
    {
    ProductID: "R412026839", 
    ConnectionMedium: "G1"
    }
]

let ASD =[{
    PressureMin: "0bar, 0psi",
    PressureMax : "16bar, 232psi",
    AmbientTemperatureMin : "-20°C, -4°F",
    AmbientTemperatureMax: "60°C, 140°F",
    MediumTemperatureMin : "-20°C, -4°F",
    MediumTemperatureMax : "60°C, 140°F",
    FlowRangeMin: "0l/min, 0m^3/h",
    FlowRangeMax: "4326l/min, 259.56m^3/h",
    FlowRangeExtended: "6590l/min, 395.4m^3/h",
    FlowRangeViewMax: "12980l/min, 778.8m^3/h",
    ProductText: "Demo_FlowMeter",
    },
    {
    ProductID: "DEMO",    
    VendorName: "AVENTICS",
    VendorText: "Emerson Automation Solutions",
    ProductName: "AFD",
    ConnectionMedium: "Selectable G3/8, G1/2, G1"
    }]

let tag = [
    {},
    { 
    DeviceName: sensorName,
    Group: group,
    Device: device,
    Owner: owner
    }
]

let assetDeploy = [
    {
    Device: deviceNumber,
    Picture: "data:image/png;base64,",
    Description:"Flow Sensor to measure the Flow Rate, Speed, Volume, Temperature, Pressure of Compressed Air, Argon (Ar), Nitrogen (N2), Helium (He) and Carbon Dioxide (CO2)",
    Geohash: "0000000000",
    Group: "Main",
    Media: "Compressed Air"
    },
    {
    Device: device,
    DeviceName: sensorName,
    ProductType: type,
    ProductVersion: version,
    Measurement: measurement,
    Owner: owner
    }
]


let flowAssets = flow.get("Assets") || []

if(flowAssets.length < 1 || flowAssets[deviceNumber] !== true ){
    asset = []
    let Assets = []
    Assets[deviceNumber] = true 
    flow.set("Assets", Assets)
    asset={}
    if (version ==="AS2"){ 
        general[0] = {...general[0], ...tag[0], ...AS2[0]}
        general[1] = {...general[1], ...tag[1], ...AS2[1]}
    }
    if (version ==="AS3"){ 
        general[0] = {...general[0], ...tag[0], ...AS3[0]}
        general[1] = {...general[1], ...tag[1], ...AS3[1]}
    }
    if (version ==="AS5"){ 
        general[0] = {...general[0], ...tag[0], ...AS5[0]}
        general[1] = {...general[1], ...tag[1], ...AS5[1]}
    }
    if (version ==="ASD"){ 
        general[0] = {...tag[0], ...ASD[0]}
        general[1] = {...tag[1], ...ASD[1]}
    }
    
    let keysGeneral = Object.keys(general[0])
    let valuesGeneral = Object.values(general[0])
    
    keysGeneral.forEach((item, index) =>{
        let fieldNew = {}
        fieldNew[item] = valuesGeneral[index]
        let payloadLabel = {}
        payloadLabel["payload"] = [fieldNew, general[1]] 
        payloadLabel["measurement"] = "AssetLabel"
        
        digitalLabel.push(payloadLabel)
    })
    
    asset.payload = general
    asset.measurement= "ASSETS"
    asset.debug = digitalLabel
}

msg.measurement = measurement

let label = []

label.payload = digitalLabel
label.measurement = "AssetLabel"



let array = []

array[0] = msg.payload
array[1] = tag[1]

msg.payload = array



msg.measurement = "AF"


return [msg,asset];
